                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34537/386b suppl.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-09T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>246. Department’s telegram no. 239, May 7, 9 p.m., and Briggs’ telephone message
                    of May 9. The War Department has informed this Department that it is cabling
                    General Ryan, Care of the Military Attaché, to the following effect: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>His visit to Cuba should be continued on an exploratory basis
                            only;</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>No discussions whatsoever regarding an agreement should be undertaken
                            with Cuban officials;</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Prior to any discussions about an agreement with the Cuban officials
                            there should be an exact understanding between the War Department and
                            this Department regarding the nature of the project.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
